WEBVTT

00:35.458 --> 00:36.339
Good morning, everyone.

00:36.359 --> 00:37.620
Thank you so much for being here.

00:38.221 --> 00:40.464
It is so good to be back.

00:41.485 --> 00:42.706
Be back at Sugar Creek.

00:43.767 --> 00:44.648
I've missed you guys.

00:45.089 --> 00:46.671
I got to tell you, it's a good thing.

00:46.811 --> 00:49.514
I enjoy disconnecting in July.

00:49.574 --> 00:52.878
To be honest, by the time I get to July, I'm ready to disconnect.

00:52.898 --> 00:56.822
And I actually do, but by the end of July, I'm starting to get homesick.

00:56.882 --> 01:01.988
I'm starting to want to get back to what God has called us to do and me to do.

01:02.108 --> 01:04.050
And so it's good to be home.

01:04.834 --> 01:07.959
I want to say a shout out to the Missouri City Campus.

01:08.400 --> 01:09.281
God bless you.

01:09.361 --> 01:10.343
Yay, God for you.

01:10.383 --> 01:13.268
And all that God is doing at Missouri City.

01:13.308 --> 01:14.970
And the same for Richmond Rosenberg.

01:15.371 --> 01:16.333
It is amazing.

01:16.373 --> 01:22.803
The blessing of God upon the Richmond Rosenberg Campus and the people that are being led to Christ there.

01:22.883 --> 01:32.178
And all of you who are watching online and worshiping the Lord with us online, we're so grateful that you're here and everybody at the Sugar Land

01:32.290 --> 01:34.974
It wasn't a great scene.

01:35.074 --> 01:37.999
Pastor Lib and Abraham again the last two weeks.

01:38.059 --> 01:38.820
Isn't he amazing?

01:39.381 --> 01:40.422
He's so amazing.

01:41.244 --> 01:45.630
He's one of the greatest pastors and preachers, I think, in America.

01:46.271 --> 01:49.756
And he's my friend and I love him to death.

01:52.140 --> 01:55.465
He took on a subject that I don't think most people would take on.

01:56.346 --> 01:57.648
Jesus in politics.

01:58.830 --> 02:01.394
Jesus in politics for the last two weeks.

02:01.538 --> 02:04.963
I thought he did just an awesome and incredible job.

02:05.303 --> 02:08.688
He didn't come down on the side of Republicans or Democrats.

02:08.728 --> 02:11.492
He came down on the side of the gospel of Jesus Christ.

02:12.113 --> 02:21.886
And it reminded us of who we are, that we are the people of God and that God has given us a purpose and a mission to accomplish.

02:22.547 --> 02:27.474
And it is eternal and it is the greatest purpose and mission of any other.

02:28.194 --> 02:41.042
And he has reminded us that when all the smoke is cleared about this presidential election that we still are the church of Jesus Christ, we still need to reach this region with a gospel of Christ.

02:41.826 --> 02:59.986
Now, today and next Sunday, Pastor Xavier, Marilyn, and I are going to address another topic that sort of dovetails with what Pastor Libbon was talking about, and the title of it is to agree, to disagree, agreeably.

03:02.722 --> 03:06.147
That title really comes from a conversation I had a couple of weeks.

03:06.307 --> 03:10.213
I mean, a couple of years ago with a member of our church, I love him.

03:10.353 --> 03:14.219
I think he is a man of honor and integrity and character.

03:14.279 --> 03:17.985
And it's a joy to call him my friend.

03:18.065 --> 03:32.306
And when we were at lunch and we were just talking about how the anger, the hatred in the country, the division in the country, he said, it used to be that people could agree to disagree.

03:33.442 --> 03:39.208
agreeably, still like each other, still, still okay with that.

03:40.350 --> 03:41.051
Where did that go?

03:41.091 --> 03:45.035
How's that been lost in this country?

03:46.397 --> 03:47.298
And I told them I don't know.

03:47.318 --> 03:49.080
I asked the same question.

03:49.620 --> 04:01.874
Americans have always been very individualistic and very opinionated, but allowed other people to have a different opinion than them without

04:02.274 --> 04:07.422
the level of hatred that we see in the culture.

04:07.442 --> 04:10.026
And now we're in a presidential election year.

04:10.486 --> 04:14.953
I got to tell you, it's the most miserable year of my life, every four years.

04:16.235 --> 04:18.819
The presidential election year.

04:20.161 --> 04:24.608
The hardest, toughest year.

04:24.628 --> 04:31.218
What both parties do, just listen to the rhetoric, what both parties do,

04:32.034 --> 04:38.381
is capitalize on fear and anger to mobilize their base.

04:38.861 --> 04:42.165
And both are doing it now, and it is what happens.

04:45.188 --> 05:01.266
But there are also media individuals, personalities, and not all media, but there are media personalities that capture, capitalize on fear and anger, night after night after night after night.

05:02.146 --> 05:04.328
It is the way to get the crowd back.

05:04.348 --> 05:07.331
It's the way to get people to come back and listen again.

05:07.832 --> 05:27.192
And what happens is they get paid on the basis of the number of people that are listening and the amount of advertising dollars that come in as a result and they're lining their pockets with millions of dollars while they are making us more afraid and more angry with each other.

05:28.493 --> 05:29.554
I got to tell you, I think

05:30.690 --> 05:34.956
The biggest promoter of feared anger is social media.

05:38.021 --> 05:53.843
Social media platforms like Google and Facebook and X and YouTube use very sophisticated algorithms to personalize our content.

05:54.424 --> 05:55.666
It begins to learn.

05:55.746 --> 05:59.811
who we are, what we think, what our opinions about different things are.

06:00.392 --> 06:10.225
And it tunes the internet to keep feeding us the same things that it knows we want to hear.

06:10.285 --> 06:23.922
And it actually, this is not just my opinion, there are studies being done about this that are being given to now a congressional committee, that it blocks us

06:24.226 --> 06:33.896
from opposing viewpoints and ends up creating an echo chamber in every one of our lives.

06:34.937 --> 06:44.047
So the only thing we hear is what we want to hear, what we want to hear, what we want to hear, and our anger and our fear grows.

06:44.728 --> 06:50.354
To the point, we began to believe things about other people that isn't true.

06:52.482 --> 06:54.966
But it is what we're being fed.

07:00.835 --> 07:06.825
The closer we get to the presidential election, this presidential election I've heard for the very first time ever in my life.

07:06.905 --> 07:07.967
It's just amazing to me.

07:08.948 --> 07:16.420
Both sides are now saying that if the other candidate gets elected, we will lose democracy.

07:16.761 --> 07:19.986
And it's both sides and both have built a case to support them.

07:25.634 --> 07:27.276
So I will tell you what I think.

07:28.758 --> 07:33.224
I think I've studied American history a lot.

07:33.244 --> 07:37.449
And I think this country has faced worse times than this right now.

07:38.130 --> 07:42.876
And we have gotten through the worst times and we have preserved our democracy.

07:42.896 --> 07:44.658
And I believe in the American people.

07:45.839 --> 07:47.141
I believe they're good people.

07:47.662 --> 07:51.026
Most of them are Christ followers.

07:55.362 --> 08:00.787
And I believe that this country will preserve democracy.

08:00.867 --> 08:02.669
It's not about one person or another.

08:07.434 --> 08:13.439
For the last 34 years, I've heard every presidential election, every single one, every single one.

08:13.800 --> 08:18.925
This next election is the most important election in American history.

08:19.565 --> 08:22.348
And every four years, it's the same.

08:22.688 --> 08:24.530
And four years from now, it'll be the same.

08:26.434 --> 08:28.436
And I have felt it.

08:29.277 --> 08:30.378
I feel it this time.

08:30.459 --> 08:32.000
I feel it next time.

08:32.301 --> 08:34.002
I have felt it all the other times.

08:35.184 --> 08:44.795
And did you know that over the last 34 years, three Republicans have been elected as president and three Democrats have been elected as president?

08:46.857 --> 08:55.026
Did you know over the last 64 years, six Democrats have been elected president and six Republicans

08:55.202 --> 08:56.724
have been elected as president.

08:58.046 --> 09:10.042
Did you know that over the last 124 years, Republicans have occupied the White House 64 years and Democrats 60 years?

09:15.569 --> 09:18.633
If I told you that I'm not worried about America, I'd be lying.

09:21.557 --> 09:25.042
But I believe in this country and I believe in this people.

09:28.802 --> 09:43.084
And I don't know how it's all going to turn out in November or four years from November, but I believe in this country and in this people.

09:46.830 --> 09:54.802
What pastor Xavier Maryland and I want to do these two Sundays is talk about

09:58.274 --> 10:03.741
coming back to agree, to disagree, agreeably.

10:06.284 --> 10:26.930
Jesus, just hours before he was crucified, prays a prayer to his heavenly Father and listen to, the prayer is found in John chapter 17 and beginning in verse 17, listen to what he says, Jesus is praying to his Father, sanctify them by your truth,

10:27.010 --> 10:28.812
Your word is truth.

10:30.494 --> 10:31.475
Now stop right there.

10:31.515 --> 10:34.839
Would you repeat this phrase with me?

10:35.519 --> 10:37.461
God's word is truth.

10:38.483 --> 10:39.043
Would you say it?

10:39.964 --> 10:41.125
God's word is truth.

10:41.306 --> 10:42.147
Would you say it again?

10:42.207 --> 10:48.774
Jesus said your word is truth.

10:49.054 --> 10:56.242
And when you grab the word of God as truth, you now have found true North.

10:57.250 --> 11:02.782
You now have found the place that you can begin in understanding the right way to go.

11:02.802 --> 11:06.751
It begins with God's Word.

11:06.972 --> 11:12.524
And this is what Jesus is saying in his prayer to his Father just hours before he's crucified verse 18.

11:12.885 --> 11:14.909
And you have sent me into the world.

11:15.270 --> 11:17.074
I have sent them into the world.

11:18.338 --> 11:22.343
For them, I sanctify myself that they too may be truly sanctified.

11:22.643 --> 11:24.485
And my prayer is not for them alone.

11:24.545 --> 11:25.606
Now, stop for a moment.

11:25.626 --> 11:27.328
He's talking about his disciples.

11:28.850 --> 11:33.515
I've lived this way so that my disciples will follow my example.

11:34.657 --> 11:35.838
But then notice what he says.

11:36.219 --> 11:42.706
And I pray also for those who will believe in me through their message.

11:44.354 --> 11:45.536
He's talking about us.

11:45.876 --> 12:01.139
It's as though Jesus in this moment looks down through time and he sees hundreds of years and thousands of years down through time and all the people that will come to know Christ as their personal Savior and I believe he sees sugar Creek Baptist Church.

12:01.760 --> 12:09.471
He sees us and he says that all of them may be one.

12:09.531 --> 12:14.258
Father, just as you are in me and I am in you,

12:16.706 --> 12:25.737
May they also be in us so that circle the words so that the world may believe that you have sent me.

12:27.860 --> 12:46.002
When the world sees Christians who disagree on some things, but are still united around what unites us, our love for Jesus Christ, our love

12:46.178 --> 12:56.951
for his word and obedience for his word and our love for the mission of God so that the world may believe that you send me.

12:58.113 --> 13:05.082
I've given them the glory that you gave me that they may be one as we are one.

13:05.122 --> 13:11.890
This morning I want to talk to you about a more controlled response.

13:12.930 --> 13:18.475
James chapter 1 verse 19 and 20 says, my dear brothers, take note of this.

13:18.696 --> 13:23.500
Everyone should be quick to listen, slow to speak, slow to become angry.

13:23.781 --> 13:29.987
For a person's anger does not bring the righteous life that God desires.

13:30.087 --> 13:41.458
And I think the first question we've got to ask is why would I even want a more controlled response because we want to bring honor to God.

13:42.338 --> 13:45.444
It's God that has brought this church together the way it is.

13:46.967 --> 13:48.309
Nobody did this.

13:48.409 --> 13:49.632
God has done this.

13:50.112 --> 14:06.002
And I believe the reason he has done this is he has brought us from every country it seems like in the world, every ethnicity, he has brought us together to be one church because he knows that to reach the region, this is the most

14:06.306 --> 14:13.497
Ethnically diverse county or one of them in the country, in order to reach the region, we got to look like the region.

14:15.820 --> 14:24.553
And I believe he is calling this church to make an impact in this region with the gospel of Jesus Christ and around this world.

14:27.678 --> 14:35.570
So I'm asking everyone who can vote, who's a citizen of the country, who can vote, to vote,

14:36.610 --> 14:38.672
in November, I'm asking you to vote.

14:39.734 --> 14:48.364
And if you're not registered, if you're a citizen of this country, you're not registered, get registered, and you can actually do that on every one of our campuses today.

14:48.824 --> 15:03.922
In the comments and the four-year of every campus, there is an official registrar or more than one who is at a table and we have organized it so you can be officially registered to vote.

15:04.290 --> 15:10.641
I'm going to try to talk you in to doing one thing or another, but just registering to vote.

15:10.661 --> 15:11.863
And I hope you'll do it.

15:12.003 --> 15:14.247
Today, you will do it.

15:14.287 --> 15:15.469
You'll register.

15:15.529 --> 15:17.012
And then in November, vote.

15:18.695 --> 15:21.499
Get involved in the political process.

15:22.902 --> 15:24.144
Learn the issues.

15:24.244 --> 15:30.034
Compare the issues to God's Word and participate.

15:31.490 --> 15:41.504
When this election is over, some people are going to be glad in this church, and some people are going to be sad, and that is pretty much a given.

15:43.908 --> 15:47.593
But when the smoke is cleared, we still have a church.

15:48.654 --> 15:55.003
We still have the call from God to reach this region and around the world, and we must do it together.

15:56.665 --> 15:59.890
The call of God on this church is bigger.

16:01.090 --> 16:02.172
than any other thing.

16:04.335 --> 16:09.704
How do we guard the treasure called Sugar Creek Baptist Church?

16:09.724 --> 16:10.645
How do we guard it?

16:11.947 --> 16:14.471
James gives us three key things.

16:14.992 --> 16:18.398
First of all, he says, be quick to hear.

16:19.219 --> 16:20.441
Be quick to hear.

16:20.942 --> 16:22.384
Be quick to hear what?

16:23.426 --> 16:28.594
Well, be quick to hear God's word on dealing with life's circumstances.

16:29.058 --> 16:37.474
Romans chapter 8 verse 28 says, we know that all things work together for good to them that love God to them that are the called according to his purpose.

16:38.215 --> 16:52.562
We know that God is sovereign, that God is in charge, that God can take any situation, any circumstance and turn it for good to those who love him and those who are the called according to his purpose.

16:56.770 --> 17:01.357
Romans 12, verse 17 and 18, never pay back evil for evil.

17:01.957 --> 17:08.146
If anyone respects what is right in the sight of all men, and as far as it depends on you, be a peace.

17:09.588 --> 17:11.811
Be a peace with everyone.

17:13.013 --> 17:13.594
I know you.

17:14.936 --> 17:16.518
I've been at this church a long time.

17:16.578 --> 17:17.600
I know who you are.

17:17.640 --> 17:19.282
I know who we are.

17:19.778 --> 17:28.668
And there is a deep desire in this church for us to honor the Lord, to honor His word, to honor His cause.

17:33.573 --> 17:38.479
Be quick to hear the facts before making a judgment call.

17:38.499 --> 17:44.786
Proverbs chapter 18 verse 13, he who gives an answer before he hears, it is a folly and shame to him.

17:45.442 --> 17:49.770
Sometimes when someone is talking to us, we assume what they're saying.

17:49.830 --> 17:52.535
We assume that they're going to say a certain thing.

17:52.556 --> 17:55.361
That's how we hear it, but it's not actually at what they said.

17:57.525 --> 18:04.518
So actually listen to the person you're talking to instead of assuming.

18:04.979 --> 18:08.626
Actually hear what they're saying.

18:10.018 --> 18:17.145
Ecclesiastes chapter 7 verse 9 says, don't be eager in your heart to be angry for anger resides in the bosom of fools.

18:17.986 --> 18:39.506
Hear both sides before you make a decision, for be quick to hear what others are actually saying, instead of trying to formulate the argument against while they're talking and not actually hearing them, actually hear them.

18:40.610 --> 18:43.413
and what they're actually saying to us.

18:44.655 --> 18:46.737
Second of all, be slow to speak.

18:46.757 --> 18:47.858
He doesn't say never speak.

18:48.359 --> 18:49.280
We've got to speak.

18:50.261 --> 18:53.405
We need to speak, but be slow to speak.

18:53.425 --> 18:55.788
Keep a close check on your tongue.

18:57.089 --> 19:04.818
Nothing destroys relationships faster than a gossiping, wagging tongue, trying to divide the hearts of people.

19:05.186 --> 19:12.617
Proverbs 15 verse 1 says, a gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger.

19:16.222 --> 19:19.547
So a gentle answer, a gentle answer.

19:20.328 --> 19:27.379
You can out-argue somebody else, out-screen somebody else, but it's not going to get you anywhere.

19:27.399 --> 19:35.090
Actually listen to the other person and answer the other person.

19:35.778 --> 19:37.640
A gentle answer turns away wrath.

19:38.922 --> 19:47.312
Psalm 17 verse one to three says, hero, Lord, this is King David writing, hero, Lord, my righteous plea, listen to my cry, give ear to my prayer.

19:47.573 --> 19:50.276
It does not rise from deceitful lips.

19:50.296 --> 19:52.419
May my vindication come from you.

19:52.659 --> 20:04.594
May your eyes see what is right, though you probe my heart and examine me at night, though you test me, you will find nothing because I have resolved that my mouth.

20:05.538 --> 20:06.440
will not sin.

20:07.922 --> 20:14.052
I think that if King David was writing this same song today, he would add three words to the song.

20:15.475 --> 20:22.046
To the verse three, I have resolved that my mouth and my fingers will not sin.

20:24.250 --> 20:31.442
It's pretty easy to hide behind a keyboard and to say the worst things, the most awful things.

20:32.194 --> 20:41.165
It's just so easy to do it because nobody's looking at you and you never speak those words to somebody else.

20:41.185 --> 20:42.606
You'd have more respect.

20:44.388 --> 20:48.293
But online and social media, oh my soul, what people say.

20:51.076 --> 20:52.598
People are following you.

20:54.300 --> 20:57.103
People that are your friends are following you.

20:57.123 --> 20:59.506
They're reading the things that you're writing.

21:00.706 --> 21:09.158
Now the truth is I am not following you and you can't follow me either because I ain't there.

21:10.419 --> 21:18.250
And I'm going to tell you why I decided that I wouldn't be there because I decided that I can save the stupidest things.

21:18.270 --> 21:26.962
I can say dumb things and I decided that I would be better off not being there and I probably would keep my job longer.

21:28.482 --> 21:31.106
So I just decided I'm not gonna participate.

21:31.146 --> 21:35.872
The only thing I'm on is what was called Twitter.

21:35.912 --> 21:38.375
Now is X, neither one of them make any sense to me.

21:39.377 --> 21:44.924
But I'm on Twitter and I'm on baseball and I'm not on anything else but baseball.

21:44.944 --> 21:46.987
That's the only thing I care about on Twitter.

21:51.273 --> 21:54.417
Do you remember what Pastor Libbon said last week?

21:54.437 --> 21:58.002
He said, look, before you write it,

21:59.778 --> 22:02.062
Pray for that person.

22:04.525 --> 22:13.079
He said, don't pray about that person, because if you pray about that person, you will eventually ask fire to come down from heaven and consume them.

22:13.099 --> 22:14.802
No, don't pray about somebody.

22:14.882 --> 22:16.104
It's not gonna probably turn out.

22:16.144 --> 22:18.347
Well, pray for someone.

22:18.367 --> 22:21.552
God, I hope this person comes to know Christ to save you.

22:21.612 --> 22:24.898
I hope this person comes to the truth of your word.

22:25.579 --> 22:27.762
I pray for this person.

22:29.858 --> 22:31.760
Stop critical gossip.

22:31.780 --> 22:36.406
Proverbs 16, 28, a perverse man stirs up dissension and gossip separates.

22:36.486 --> 22:40.911
Close friends, lovingly confront.

22:43.113 --> 22:44.195
He didn't say never speak.

22:44.335 --> 22:45.957
There's times that we need to speak.

22:46.377 --> 22:48.219
There's times that we need to confront.

22:48.540 --> 22:57.490
But the confrontation that we have with someone else needs to be designed to restore the relationship, not retaliate,

22:59.522 --> 23:17.773
Proverbs, chapter 16, verse 28 says, a perverse man stirs up dissensions, gossip separates close friends, lovingly confront Jesus said in Matthew 1815, if your brother sends against you, go and show him his fault just between the two of you.

23:17.994 --> 23:20.578
In other words, don't call five people before you go.

23:20.598 --> 23:25.266
Go to your brother, your sister,

23:26.306 --> 23:36.076
Just you and that person and if your brother, your sister listens to you've won your brother over and that's the goal, the goal of restoration.

23:38.318 --> 23:43.284
Be swift to hear and slow to speak and slow to anger.

23:44.485 --> 23:48.869
Learn how to ignore petty disagreements.

23:49.430 --> 23:53.394
You can't fight over every hill, not every hill is to die for.

23:55.586 --> 23:57.429
Find the things that really matter.

23:58.931 --> 24:00.133
And let the other things go.

24:00.173 --> 24:06.563
Proverbs 8, 1911 says, a man's discretion makes him slow to anger, and it's his glory to overlook and offense.

24:07.925 --> 24:09.908
You don't have to answer everything that happens.

24:09.948 --> 24:19.463
And in fact, 1 Peter, chapter 4, verse 8 says, above all, love each other deeply because love covers over a multitude of sins.

24:20.905 --> 24:21.586
Let it go.

24:23.522 --> 24:26.026
There are some things we cannot let it go.

24:26.066 --> 24:28.108
There are some things we must confront.

24:29.270 --> 24:36.781
They matter, they're important, and we need to deal with them, but not in a way in which we beat somebody else up, but in a way we try to restore.

24:38.924 --> 24:40.366
We try to break through.

24:40.386 --> 24:51.922
One of the things that I've experienced in this church that has been a great time

24:52.514 --> 25:07.829
A great time for me is talking to individuals who think differently than I think politically, and about specific issues, and sitting down, I've sat down with, I don't know how many people just talked.

25:10.571 --> 25:14.735
I'm not gonna try to convert you, you're not gonna convert me, but I just wanna talk.

25:15.095 --> 25:17.217
I've got questions I wanna ask.

25:17.237 --> 25:22.002
You got questions, you asked them, and to actually sit and talk

25:22.114 --> 25:23.095
to another person.

25:23.876 --> 25:26.540
I've discovered so much misinformation.

25:32.507 --> 25:35.010
I've discovered people willing to do that.

25:35.090 --> 25:36.192
Just don't shout at me.

25:38.635 --> 25:39.356
Just talk.

25:41.018 --> 25:42.960
And I'm willing to listen to your side.

25:44.943 --> 25:47.506
Learn how to develop safeguards

25:48.130 --> 25:53.859
Ephesians, chapter four, verse 26 and 27, be angry and yet do not sin.

25:54.160 --> 25:58.827
Do not let the sun go down upon your anger and do not give the devil an opportunity.

25:59.087 --> 26:00.369
What is he saying?

26:00.630 --> 26:04.276
He's saying first, limit the duration of your anger.

26:06.539 --> 26:07.561
Deal with the anger.

26:08.422 --> 26:11.908
Don't keep it going because the longer you nurse at the deeper it grows.

26:14.071 --> 26:15.794
And limit the intensity.

26:15.970 --> 26:19.135
the intensity and the duration of your anger.

26:19.436 --> 26:23.703
And if you do this, you will not give Satan a foothold in your life.

26:25.607 --> 26:29.373
Don't give in to a deepening anger.

26:31.637 --> 26:36.786
Deal with it, but in a way that does not give Satan an opportunity.

26:36.994 --> 26:40.618
Here's what God is saying to us in this political season.

26:40.919 --> 27:01.042
Learn how to listen, learn how to hold your tongue, learn how to give your mind and heart a chance to catch up before you react and then speak a more controlled response.

27:04.098 --> 27:08.964
There's a church that has existed now for a long time.

27:09.084 --> 27:13.429
It's in Austria and his story is pretty amazing.

27:13.790 --> 27:19.597
Here is this church and they have a teeny little bit of property between a hill and a road.

27:20.337 --> 27:22.180
And so they build their church.

27:22.200 --> 27:30.770
Well, the thing is, is that the church keeps growing and they're out of space and they don't know what to do because they've got a road right in front of their church.

27:32.642 --> 27:46.537
So they decided to build another part of the church on the other side of the road and look at what it looks like.

27:46.557 --> 27:47.558
I think it's ridiculous.

27:49.020 --> 27:51.803
I think to myself, surely they could have come up with a better idea.

27:55.287 --> 28:02.194
What you can't see very well from the picture is, you see a balcony on the left hand side, actually that whole wall

28:02.594 --> 28:09.545
You can remove on Sunday morning and over on the right hand side, you can remove that wall on Sunday morning.

28:09.986 --> 28:23.107
The pastor speaks from the building on the left and he yells, the people that are on the right, I'm not kidding, I'm serious.

28:23.788 --> 28:29.938
And every time a car comes by, he's got to stop the sermon because they can't hear him over the car.

28:32.898 --> 28:34.801
And I'm thinking this is ridiculous.

28:37.145 --> 28:38.487
But here's what I'm asking you.

28:41.032 --> 28:45.098
Don't make that be sugar creek by November.

28:56.057 --> 28:59.122
I sort of think that most people are entrenched already.

29:05.730 --> 29:11.137
and not everybody agrees with you, and not everybody agrees with me.

29:17.084 --> 29:25.153
In the process of walking through these days, hold firm to what you know from God's word is true.

29:29.238 --> 29:35.666
This church has taken what Jesus has said to us

29:36.578 --> 29:38.942
truth and grace.

29:42.528 --> 29:45.934
Not one without the other, both end.

29:47.557 --> 29:50.522
Truth and grace.

29:52.866 --> 29:57.874
Ephesians chapter 4 verse 2 and 3 says this, always be humble and gentle.

29:59.714 --> 30:04.779
Be patient with each other, making allowance for each other's faults because of your love.

30:05.159 --> 30:09.624
Make every effort to keep yourselves united in the spirit.

30:12.286 --> 30:16.510
Binding yourselves together with peace.

30:20.074 --> 30:22.736
A more controlled response.

30:25.959 --> 30:26.380
Let's pray.

30:27.060 --> 30:28.882
Father, we come to you today

30:29.026 --> 30:43.948
Oh God, you know my heart and you know how worried I feel and I'm not supposed to be worrying.

30:48.254 --> 30:56.466
You know how anxious, not just I feel, but all of us probably depending on the level of involvement.

31:03.170 --> 31:07.775
God, we ask that you would be God of this moment.

31:14.001 --> 31:15.463
None of us are God.

31:17.925 --> 31:19.126
Only you are God.

31:20.668 --> 31:23.531
And we ask that you would be God of this moment.

31:25.953 --> 31:30.578
And that you would bring

31:31.490 --> 31:34.633
our country back together.

31:39.738 --> 31:50.288
But, oh God, of all people, you would bring and keep us together.

31:53.070 --> 32:01.138
For after November, we are still a church, and we still have a mission to love

32:01.346 --> 32:06.518
and lead all people to life change in Christ.

32:09.946 --> 32:11.751
Bless us and help us.

32:13.936 --> 32:19.609
I pray in Jesus' name, amen.

32:19.629 --> 32:20.050
Amen.

